    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2006-05-16</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2006-06-13T17:22:05Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Commission on Economic Indicators Act of 2006 - Establishes the Commission on Economic Indicators to study and report to Congress on: (1) economic statistics collected and reported by U.S. government agencies, including national income, employment and unemployment, wages, personal income, wealth, savings, debt, productivity, inflation, and international trade and capital flows; and (2) ways to improve the related statistical measurements so that they provide a more accurate and complete depiction of economic conditions.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
